# PUBLIC_INTERFACE
# Example environment variables for the React frontend to reach the backend API.
# Copy this file to ".env" and adjust values as needed.

# Preferred in production: full URL to the backend API
# Example for the running backend (update if different):
# REACT_APP_API_BASE_URL=https://vscode-internal-31796-beta.beta01.cloud.kavia.ai:3001

# In development with CRA dev server, you can rely on the proxy by setting:
# REACT_APP_PROXY_TARGET=https://vscode-internal-31796-beta.beta01.cloud.kavia.ai:3001

# Notes:
# - If REACT_APP_API_BASE_URL is set, the frontend will call the backend directly.
# - If REACT_APP_API_BASE_URL is NOT set, the frontend uses "/api" and expects the dev proxy (setupProxy.js)
#   to forward "/api/*" to REACT_APP_PROXY_TARGET (and strip the "/api" prefix).
# - Do not commit real secrets here; this file is for documentation and examples only.
